      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(qqbot): persist group inbound delivery route for announce target resolution",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n**Problem**: The `event.type !== \"c2c\"` guard at `extensions/qqbot/src/engine/gateway/outbound-dispatch.ts:444` allows `dm` (direct message) events to also persist route via `updateLastRoute`, because `event.type` can be `\"dm\"` and `\"dm\" !== \"c2c\"` evaluates to `true`. This means QQ Bot direct messages unintentionally overwrite the session deliveryContext, which can cause group announce routing to target the DM conversation instead of the correct group.\n\n**Solution**: Change the guard from `event.type !== \"c2c\"` to `event.type === \"group\" || event.type === \"guild\"`, explicitly gating route persistence to only group and guild turns. This is the correct positive-match approach — only events from group/guild conversations should persist their delivery route for later announce target resolution. DM events (both `c2c` and `dm` types) are unconditionally excluded.\n\n**What changed**: Two files:\n1. `extensions/qqbot/src/engine/gateway/outbound-dispatch.ts:444` — Changed condition from `event.type !== \"c2c\"` to `event.type === \"group\" || event.type === \"guild\"`\n2. `extensions/qqbot/src/engine/gateway/outbound-dispatch.test.ts` — Added 4 focused test cases covering all four event types:\n\n| Test | Event type | Expected behavior |\n|------|-----------|-------------------|\n| skips updateLastRoute for c2c events | `c2c` | No route persistence |\n| skips updateLastRoute for dm events | `dm` | No route persistence |\n| persists updateLastRoute for group events | `group` | Route persisted |\n| persists updateLastRoute for guild events | `guild` | Route persisted |\n\n**What did NOT change**: No changes to existing announce message creation logic, other dispatch paths, Gateway session management, npm dependencies, or test infrastructure.\n\n## Evidence\n\n**Unit test results** — All 27 tests passed including the 4 new focused tests:\n\n```\n$ pnpm test extensions/qqbot/src/engine/gateway/outbound-dispatch.test.ts\n\n RUN  v4.1.8\n\n Test Files  1 passed (1)\n      Tests  27 passed (27)\n   Start at  21:03:27\n   Duration  19.74s\n\n[test] passed 1 Vitest shard in 26.05s\n```\n\n**Proof logic** — The test harness exercises `dispatchOutbound` with each of the four event types (`c2c`, `dm`, `group`, `guild`) and inspects the `record` object passed to `recordInboundSession`. The `updateLastRoute` key is only present in the record for `group` and `guild` events. For `c2c` and `dm` events, the record contains no `updateLastRoute` property.\n\nThis proves:\n- ✅ `group` and `guild` events persist route via `updateLastRoute`\n- ✅ `c2c` events skip route persistence\n- ✅ `dm` events **also** skip route persistence (the defect in the original `!== \"c2c\"` guard)\n- ✅ No regression in existing test coverage (all original tests pass)\n\n**Real QQ Bot E2E testing note**: This fix is in the QQ Bot channel plugin, which requires real QQ credentials to run end-to-end. Full E2E proof with live Gateway logs is not available because we do not have access to the QQ Bot app credentials (`appId`, `token`, `secret`) needed to connect to the QQ Bot WebSocket API. The unit tests provide structural coverage of the route-logic change, and the code change is a straightforward condition swap from a negative-match (`!== \"c2c\"`) to a positive-match (`=== \"group\" || === \"guild\"`) — a mechanical correctness improvement that is fully verified by tests.\n\n## Risk checklist\n\n- [x] **merge-risk**: Low. Single condition change in one guard expression. The new guard is strictly more restrictive — it excludes `dm` events that the old guard incorrectly allowed. No existing dispatch logic is modified, no control flow is altered, no error paths change.\n- [x] This change is backwards compatible. All existing functionality continues to work; the only behavior change is that `dm` events (which were incorrectly persisting routes) now match the intended behavior of being excluded.\n- [x] This change has been tested. All 27 tests pass, including 4 new focused tests covering every event type.\n- [ ] Breaking changes (if any) are documented in Summary\n",
        "branch": "fix/issue-86387-qqbot-group-route-persistence",
